title: Israel approves law to strip Arab attackers of citizenship
description: Israel's parliament has overwhelmingly approved a law to strip Arabs of their Israeli citizenship or residency if they are convicted in nationalistic attacks or give money to prisoners.

title: Sunak pledges further £25m in aid from UK for earthquake victims
description: Rishi Sunak has said the UK government's pledge of a further £25m towards the relief effort following the devastating earthquake in Syria and Turkey will provide "vital humanitarian assistance" to victims.

title: 'The whole room slid': Sisters 'lost hope' before being rescued from rubble after four days
description: Two sisters who spent more than four days trapped in the rubble of their collapsed apartment say the whole block slid in one direction as last week's enormous earthquake struck in southern Turkey.

title: Six days in Turkey, three lives saved: British volunteer reflects on rescue mission
description: Rob Davis has just saved three people's lives.

title: NATO's focus is on heavy weapons and training for Ukraine - not sending fighter jets
description: After two days of diplomacy and negotiations, NATO's meeting broke up with lots of ideas, but no deal to send fighter jets to Ukraine.

title: War in Ukraine has wiped out half of Russia's modern battle tanks, say experts
description: The war in Ukraine has wiped out half of Russia's fleet of modern battle tanks, say analysts presenting their annual assessment of military power in the world.

title: Captain of boys' football team rescued from Thai cave in 2018 dies in UK
description: One of the 12 boys who was rescued from a Thai cave after being trapped for two weeks in 2018 has died in the UK.

title: British man who died in Ukraine named as 'hero' paramedic Jonathan Shenkin
description: A British man who was killed in Ukraine has been named as Jonathan Shenkin.

title: Child among four dead after cyclone hits New Zealand
description: At least four people have died - including a child - after Cyclone Gabrielle caused extensive flooding and landslides in New Zealand.

title: Gunman who killed three at university 'may have planned school attacks' - as details of victims emerge
description: The gunman who shot dead three people at Michigan State University may have also been planning to attack two schools, according to police.

title: Pilot pictured after being taken hostage by Indonesia rebels who burnt his plane
description: A New Zealand pilot taken hostage by separatist rebels in Indonesia has been pictured alive in images released by the group.

title: Mystery objects shot down by US were 'probably benign'
description: Three objects shot down by fighter jets over North America in the past week probably had a "commercial or benign" purpose, the White House has admitted.

title: Ten years on from meteor 'wake-up call', how safe are we from a potentially catastrophic strike?
description: It wasn't quite the day the Earth stood still, but those who witnessed a fiery asteroid briefly outshine the sun as it soared towards the Russian city of Chelyabinsk will almost certainly never forget it.
